{"title_page": "Wayne Garfield", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Wayne Garfield\n| image       = \n| image_size  =\n| caption     =\n| birth_date  = \n| birth_place = \n| residence   = \n| nationality = United States\n| education   = \n| occupation  = songwriter, vocalist, producer\n| spouse      = \n| partner     =\n| children    = \n| parents     =\n| relatives   =\n| signature   =\n| website     = \n| footnotes   =\n}}\n\n'''Wayne Garfield''' is a composer, collaborating songwriter, vocalist, social entrepreneur, community activists, and producer for four decades. He is a contributor, and co founder of the vaunted music collective [[Change (band)]], contributing to musical pop culture. Chance launched the career of [[Luther Vandross]] with the hit song \"[[The Glow of Love]]\". Which became #1 on the [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] Dance/Disco Chart in the summer of 1980.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.spiritmusicgroup.com/Clients/Library/Wayne-Garfield|title=Spirit Music Group &#124; Wayne Garfield|website=www.spiritmusicgroup.com|accessdate=Apr 13, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924170725/http://www.spiritmusicgroup.com/Clients/Library/Wayne-Garfield|archive-date=September 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.writersrulecoalition.org/about_us|title=FOUNDER|website=Wrc200|accessdate=Apr 13, 2020}}</ref> <ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=NMSKDwAAQBAJ&lpg=PT70&ots=IfmS4-buYF&dq=wayne%20garfield%20vocalist&pg=PT70#v=onepage&q=wayne%20garfield%20&f=false</ref>\n\n==Career==\nGarfield's career started as a singer with the [[The Voices of East Harlem]] a rock and soul group. The group was formed in 1969 in Harlem, New York City.  The group recorded with [[Elektra Records|Elektra]], Just Sunshine, and [[Motown]]. The Voices of East Harlem was a 20-member ensemble aged 12 to 21. The group worked with producers [[Leroy Hutson]] and [[Curtis Mayfield]]. \nGarfield was a member of the [[Change (band)]] collected. He has composed music for [[Janet Jackson]], [[Luther Vandross]], [[Roy Ayers]], [[Kurtis Blow]], [[Taj Mahal]], [[Dee Dee Bridgewater]],  soundtrack for the movie Coffy, Salt-N-Pepa, [[Aretha Franklin]], [[Theo Croker]], and [[Fela Kuti]]. He has functioned in the capacity of composer, lyricist, manager and arranger for three decades. In 1973 Garfield wrote the soundtrack and vocals for the movie [[Coffy]]. The movie was directed by [[Jack Hill]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://secondhandsongs.com/artist/19425|title=Songs written by Wayne Garfield &#124; SecondHandSongs|website=secondhandsongs.com|accessdate=Apr 13, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tidal.com/browse/artist/6739475|title=Wayne Garfield|website=TIDAL Browse|accessdate=Apr 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\nHe has worked with [[Angela Winbush]] and Debye Burrell to develop their careers.\n\nIn 1986 Garfield united [[Kurtis Blow]] and [[Bob Dylan]] in producing \"Street Rock\", which became a hip-hop crossover.\n\nIn 2002,  Garfield formed the advocacy group \"Writers Rule Coalition\", for songwriters to gain award recognition.\n\nIn 2003, the National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences Board of Trustees awarded the Winners Certificate to songwriters and producers of Grammy nominated and winning recordings containing samples. Which gave writers and producers recognition for their contribution.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Composer===\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* 2019\tEverything and More: The Complete Collection 1980\u20132019; (Change Collective) \t\n* 2018\tKOD; J. Cole\t\n* 2016\tEscape Velocity; Theo Croker\t\n* 2014\tThe Box Set Series; Luther Vandross\t\n* 2013\t12\" Disco: The Collection\t\t\n* 2011\tLove & Revolution; Nicola Conte\t\n* 2010\tBest of Number Ones; Janet Jackson\t\n* 2010\tIcon: Number Ones; Janet Jackson\t\n* 2009\tLouder;\tBig Ali\tRecording\n* 2009\tNumber Ones; Janet Jackson\t\n* 2009\tOld School Jams, Vol. 8\t\t\n* 2009\tThe Best; Janet Jackson\t\n* 2008\tDrew's Famous Just D