las, and Curtis Axel|url=http://prowrestling.net/site/2017/08/20/0820-powells-wwe-summerslam-kickoff-show-coverage-new-day-vs-usos-smackdown-tag-titles-akira-tozawa-vs-neville-wwe-cruiserweight-championship-matt-hardy-jeff-hardy/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=August 20, 2017}}</ref>\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 7\n|champion = {{sort|New|[[The New Day (professional wrestling)|The New Day]]}}<br />{{small|([[Big E (wrestler)|Big E]], [[Kofi Kingston]], and [[Xavier Woods]])}}\n|reign    = 2\n|date     = {{dts|September 12, 2017}}\n|days     = {{age in days nts|September 12, 2017|October 8, 2017}}\n|days2    = {{age in days nts|September 12, 2017|October 7, 2017}}\n|location = [[Las Vegas|Las Vegas, NV]]\n|event    = ''[[SmackDown]]''\n|notes    = This was a [[Professional wrestling match types#Hardcore-based variations|Sin City Street Fight]].<br>Big E and Kingston won the match, but Woods was also recognized as champion under the [[Freebird Rule]].\n|ref      = <ref name=\"SmackDown09122017\">{{cite web|last=Keller|first=Wade|title=Keller's WWE Smackdown Report 9/12: Vince McMahon appears to address Shane being suspended and Owens threatening to sue|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2017/09/12/kellers-wwe-smackdown-report-912-vince-mcmahon-appears-address-shane-suspended-owens-threatening-sue/|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=September 12, 2017}}</ref>\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 8\n|champion = {{sort|Usos|[[The Usos]]}}<br />{{small|([[Jey Uso]] and [[Jimmy Uso]])}}\n|reign    = 3\n|date     = {{dts|October 8, 2017}}\n|days     = {{age in days nts|October 8, 2017|April 8, 2018}}\n|days2    = {{age in days nts|October 8, 2017|April 8, 2018}}\n|location = [[Detroit|Detroit, MI]]\n|event    = [[Hell in a Cell (2017)|Hell in a Cell]]\n|notes    = This was a [[Hell in a Cell|Hell in a Cell match]].<br>[[Big E (wrestler)|Big E]] and [[Xavier Woods]] represented [[The New Day (wrestling)|The New Day]].\n|ref      = <ref name=\"HIAC2017\">{{cite web|last=Powel